WEBVTT

01:04.958 --> 01:06.250
Hello?

01:06.250 --> 01:07.583
<i>Callum.</i>

01:09.291 --> 01:13.000
<i>I want you
to meet me in 15 minutes.</i>

01:13.958 --> 01:16.750
What? Tonight? Now?

01:17.333 --> 01:20.166
<i>- At this location.</i>

01:21.375 --> 01:23.583
Uh, no, I... I don't think
I can make that in time.

01:23.583 --> 01:25.458
<i>Fine.</i>

01:25.458 --> 01:29.375
<i>I mean, I'm happy to text your girlfriend
the screenshots if you like</i>,

01:29.375 --> 01:31.375
<i>or, uh, or your mum.</i>

01:31.375 --> 01:32.541
No, don't.

01:32.541 --> 01:34.833
Please don't tell my mum.

01:34.833 --> 01:37.041
<i>Well, then, be here in 15 minutes,</i>

01:37.041 --> 01:41.250
<i>or everyone in your contact list
will get the screenshots.</i>

02:03.375 --> 02:04.500
Shit.

02:05.500 --> 02:06.666
Not now. No.

02:12.500 --> 02:14.791
<i>- Emergency. What service do you require?</i>
- Yeah, uh, hello?

02:14.791 --> 02:18.291
<i>- Fire, police or ambulance?</i>
- Uh, ambulance, please. Um...

02:19.208 --> 02:22.125
Uh, maybe police. There's been a crash.

02:22.125 --> 02:23.208
Uh...

02:23.208 --> 02:24.916
No, there's someone in the road.

02:25.833 --> 02:28.541
A man.
Uh, maybe someone in the car.

02:29.375 --> 02:30.958
I think they're, um...

02:33.166 --> 02:34.208
Okay.

02:35.250 --> 02:36.291
Yeah.

02:37.208 --> 02:38.916
Yeah. I... I can check.

02:39.833 --> 02:42.041
Uh, the man in the road is, um...

02:44.875 --> 02:47.416
No. No, I don't think he is.

02:49.833 --> 02:52.458
Okay. Just stay on the line.

02:53.333 --> 02:55.041
Just don't leave me alone.

03:01.791 --> 03:04.000
-  Shit.

03:04.000 --> 03:07.625
No, the passenger... looks really bad.

03:09.500 --> 03:10.791
No, it looks like they've...

03:13.875 --> 03:15.083
Shit.

03:34.416 --> 03:35.958
-  Morning.
- There you go.

03:35.958 --> 03:39.916
Cerys Jones, city banker, high achiever,

03:39.916 --> 03:41.833
disappeared seven years ago.

03:41.833 --> 03:43.416
Suspected suicide.

03:44.166 --> 03:45.750
So where's she been?

03:45.750 --> 03:49.000
Well, from
what we can tell, on ice.

03:51.333 --> 03:52.750
What, for seven years?

03:52.750 --> 03:56.208
Well, we won't know for how long
until we can run proper tests.

03:57.041 --> 03:57.875
And the car?

03:58.791 --> 04:02.458
Reported stolen.
South London, ten days ago.

04:02.458 --> 04:05.083
What about the lad that called it in?
What's his name? Um...

04:06.458 --> 04:07.291
Aldrich?

04:07.791 --> 04:08.666
Callum.

04:10.125 --> 04:11.250
What was he doing here?

04:11.750 --> 04:14.000
Yeah, well, that's the question.

04:14.583 --> 04:16.500
He left work to drive here

04:16.500 --> 04:19.000
for no reason
that we've been able to establish.

04:19.833 --> 04:21.750
Saw the site, called 999,

04:21.750 --> 04:23.541
and then evaporated.

04:33.791 --> 04:37.458
This isn't a case of wrong place
at the wrong time, is it?

04:38.625 --> 04:39.750
Someone wanted him here.

04:39.750 --> 04:41.500
Sorry. We can't let you through.

04:41.500 --> 04:43.875
I have to. I've been waiting too long.

04:44.541 --> 04:45.750
Who's that?

04:45.750 --> 04:48.666
It's the mother. Corinne.

04:51.208 --> 04:55.000
Corinne, hi. I'm DCI Luther.

04:55.000 --> 04:56.625
I'm in charge of finding your son.

04:56.625 --> 04:57.666
Where is he?

04:57.666 --> 04:59.750
Well, we don't know. Not yet.

04:59.750 --> 05:01.250
This scene is...

05:01.250 --> 05:02.541
It's... it's unusual.

05:02.541 --> 05:06.875
My son is out there somewhere right now.
So you need to find him.

05:06.875 --> 05:09.833
-  I'll do the very best I can.
-  It's not good enough.

05:09.833 --> 05:11.708
I need you to promise me.

05:12.291 --> 05:14.625
I need you to promise me
you'll find Callum.

05:19.708 --> 05:20.708
Okay.

05:21.708 --> 05:22.791
I promise.

05:23.375 --> 05:25.750
I'll bring your boy home. Okay?

05:26.583 --> 05:28.458
Now, try not to worry too much.

05:48.333 --> 05:49.583
No, no, no relax.

05:49.583 --> 05:52.541
This isn't about you
and your predilections.

05:52.541 --> 05:56.083
There's this chap,
Detective Chief Inspector Luther.

05:56.875 --> 06:00.291
And he's in charge of finding
this poor young lad Callum,

06:00.791 --> 06:03.083
and I can't allow that to happen,
I'm afraid.

06:04.916 --> 06:06.250
Now, listen, listen.

06:07.208 --> 06:09.916
From what I hear,
DCI Luther's a bit of a bad apple.

06:10.416 --> 06:13.541
Trouble is, he's a very analog bad apple.

06:13.541 --> 06:16.000
Doesn't have what you might call
an online presence,

06:16.000 --> 06:18.750
which is why I'm calling you.

06:20.166 --> 06:23.666
I want everything on him.

06:24.458 --> 06:27.000
Every furtive little secret,

06:27.750 --> 06:29.833
every intimate disgrace.

06:31.208 --> 06:34.041
<i>I want his corruption.</i>

06:35.166 --> 06:37.666
<i>I want evidence of any misstep.</i>

06:37.666 --> 06:39.583
<i>Any wrongdoing.</i>

06:41.083 --> 06:43.000
<i>Any line he's crossed.</i>

06:44.583 --> 06:48.208
I want... his shame.

07:04.083 --> 07:07.250
Extraordinary scenes today
outside London's Old Bailey,

07:07.250 --> 07:11.333
where following the release to the media
of an apparently incriminating dossier,

07:11.333 --> 07:12.708
DCI John Luther,

07:12.708 --> 07:15.375
<i>a storied police officer,
is appearing in a multitude</i>

07:15.375 --> 07:17.166
<i>of serious criminal charges.</i>

07:17.166 --> 07:20.416
<i>And yet he now stands charged
with a shocking catalog of crimes</i>

07:20.416 --> 07:24.208
<i>including breaking and entering,
suspect intimidation,</i>

07:24.208 --> 07:26.125
<i>tampering with evidence, bribery.</i>

07:26.125 --> 07:31.208
<i>A litany of alleged vigilante activity
that critics say attest to a man</i>

07:31.208 --> 07:34.916
<i>who felt entitled
to take justice into his own hands</i>...

07:34.916 --> 07:38.750
<i>Detective Chief Inspector John Luther
was in charge of the hunt</i>

07:38.750 --> 07:41.083
<i>for missing London teenager Callum Aldrich</i>

07:41.083 --> 07:42.708
<i>at the time of his arrest.</i>

07:42.708 --> 07:45.958
<i>Since when,
London police have been heavily criticized</i>

07:45.958 --> 07:48.750
<i>for the lack of progress in this case.</i>

07:48.750 --> 07:52.750
<i>DCI Luther had recently apprehended
husband and wife serial killers</i>

07:52.750 --> 07:54.583
<i>Jeremy and Vivian Lake</i>,

07:54.583 --> 07:57.916
<i>whilst leading the hunt
for the missing teenager Callum Aldrich.</i>

07:57.916 --> 08:01.291
<i>...for the metropolitan police commented
that the search for Callum Aldrich</i>

08:01.291 --> 08:03.458
<i>remains their highest priority.</i>

08:03.458 --> 08:04.958
Good luck with that, now, mate.

08:04.958 --> 08:07.541
<i>...we expect
to see Luther being driven out</i>

08:07.541 --> 08:09.416
<i>through the gates of the Old Bailey</i>

08:09.416 --> 08:13.583
<i>to begin a lengthy sentence
at Hawksmoor maximum security prison.</i>

08:13.583 --> 08:16.083
-  Here he comes! Here he comes!

08:20.458 --> 08:22.541
-  Hey, Luther! Luther!

08:26.625 --> 08:29.583
<i>As a former police officer,
what life will be like for him there</i>

08:29.583 --> 08:31.333
<i>is anybody's guess.</i>

08:34.500 --> 08:40.750
Okay, then.
I think we are about ready to go.

09:11.416 --> 09:13.875
 Stand up if you hate police!

09:13.875 --> 09:16.541
Stand up if you hate police!

09:16.541 --> 09:19.000
- Stand up if you hate police!

09:19.000 --> 09:21.875
 Stand up if you hate police!

09:21.875 --> 09:22.875
Hurry up.

09:22.875 --> 09:24.458
 ...if you hate police!

09:24.458 --> 09:29.833
 Stand up if you hate police!
Stand up if you hate police!

09:29.833 --> 09:32.166
- Stand up if you hate police!

09:32.166 --> 09:33.458
Come on, let's go.

09:34.291 --> 09:37.041
Out of the way. Come on. Move! Move!

09:38.333 --> 09:39.458
Come on.

09:39.458 --> 09:42.000
-  Fuck you, copper.
- Move. Get out of the way!

09:43.166 --> 09:44.458
Back up!

09:44.458 --> 09:47.125
-  Come on.

09:54.791 --> 09:57.125
-  Watch your back, copper.
- Fuck off.

09:58.666 --> 10:01.875
-  Come on. Let's get moving.

10:30.916 --> 10:32.166
Hello.

10:32.166 --> 10:33.166
<i>Mum?</i>

10:34.458 --> 10:35.500
Who is this?

10:36.000 --> 10:38.166
<i>- Mum, can you come and get me?</i>
- Who is this?

10:39.000 --> 10:39.833
<i>Mum, it's me.</i>

10:39.833 --> 10:42.791
Callum? Is it really you? Callum?

11:38.458 --> 11:39.416
Callum?

11:44.750 --> 11:47.125
<i>Hey, it's Callum.
Sorry I missed your call.</i>

11:47.125 --> 11:49.166
<i>Uh, leave me a message
at the sound of the beep.</i>

11:53.458 --> 11:54.541
Hello?

12:04.875 --> 12:05.875
Callum?

12:07.375 --> 12:09.083
Callum, it's me. It's Mum.

12:14.041 --> 12:16.625
<i>Hey, it's Callum.
Sorry I missed your call.</i>

12:20.166 --> 12:21.333
Callum.

12:27.000 --> 12:28.291
<i>Hey, it's Callum...</i>

14:11.958 --> 14:15.416
DCI Raine. Yep. Okay.

14:20.208 --> 14:22.833
Back up, please. Back up.

14:22.833 --> 14:25.708
<i>Our reporter,
John Cunningham, is at the scene.</i>

14:25.708 --> 14:28.291
<i>Details are sketchy at this stage.</i>

14:28.291 --> 14:31.916
<i>The scene is tightly cordoned off,
but there are unconfirmed reports</i>

14:31.916 --> 14:34.541
<i>that a number of bodies
have been found in the house.</i>

14:35.583 --> 14:37.708
<i>We're awaiting confirmation
that one of the bodies</i>

14:37.708 --> 14:40.791
<i>is that of the missing teenager
Callum Aldrich.</i>

14:40.791 --> 14:43.208
<i>The police are yet to issue
any official information.</i>

15:02.000 --> 15:03.041
<i>Eight victims.</i>

15:03.041 --> 15:05.541
Each officially a missing person
until last night.

15:05.541 --> 15:07.375
The house belongs to a Saudi national

15:07.375 --> 15:10.083
who hasn't set foot on British soil
in five years.

15:10.083 --> 15:12.416
Our killer must've known that.
Let's find out how.

15:13.000 --> 15:15.000
Earliest crime goes back 11 years.

15:15.000 --> 15:17.458
The most recent dates back to last year.

15:17.458 --> 15:20.416
So, where were
the bodies stored in the interim?

15:20.416 --> 15:24.000
And who would have
the kind of space, time, or money

15:24.000 --> 15:25.500
to do something like that?

15:25.500 --> 15:28.791
This has been carefully planned
and executed over a number of years,

15:28.791 --> 15:30.500
so there'll be a lot of data to parse.

15:30.500 --> 15:31.583
But...

15:32.291 --> 15:37.375
you find me one point of commonality
between these victims, just one,

15:38.916 --> 15:41.125
- and you'll have our killer.
-  Yes, ma'am.

15:41.250 --> 15:42.208
Let's get to it.

15:43.541 --> 15:44.750
Find me that connection.

16:19.083 --> 16:20.125
Shit.

16:31.416 --> 16:34.541
<i>No, no, no!</i>

16:36.250 --> 16:37.208
<i>Mum!</i>

16:38.958 --> 16:41.416
<i>Mum! Ah! Ah! Please stop!</i>

16:44.791 --> 16:47.541
<i>Hello again, John.</i>

16:49.500 --> 16:52.500
<i>Do you know who that was?
Oh, I'll bet you do.</i>

16:52.500 --> 16:54.125
<i>Oh, poor Callum.</i>

16:55.791 --> 16:58.333
<i>You know, I had him.</i>

16:58.333 --> 17:00.666
<i>Yeah, I had him tucked away,</i>

17:01.333 --> 17:05.333
<i>and I stood next to you at a bus stop.</i>

17:06.208 --> 17:09.541
<i>Offered you a mint, and you took it.</i>

17:10.791 --> 17:15.708
<i>I looked you right in the eye
'cause I was curious.</i>

17:16.458 --> 17:21.041
<i>I wanted to know if you'd see it in me.</i>

17:21.750 --> 17:25.583
<i>Because that is who you are, isn't it?</i>

17:25.583 --> 17:30.625
<i>The man who knows
all about people like me.</i>

17:31.875 --> 17:34.125
<i>But you didn't see me.</i>

17:35.791 --> 17:40.750
<i>And now you are in a cage
because I put you there.</i>

17:42.500 --> 17:47.333
<i>It makes me wonder how you're gonna feel,
having to watch what happens next.</i>

17:51.416 --> 17:52.333
You all right?

17:53.500 --> 17:54.791
Tickety-boo.

17:55.750 --> 17:57.375
Someone's here to see you.

18:00.583 --> 18:01.666
Who?

18:01.666 --> 18:03.625
Barbra Streisand. Fuck do I know?

18:17.291 --> 18:18.375
Corinne?

18:19.958 --> 18:22.041
Well, you remembered my name at least.

18:24.166 --> 18:26.125
Of course I remember your name.

18:28.875 --> 18:30.791
Corinne, what are you doing here?

18:37.208 --> 18:38.541
Corinne, I'm so...

18:38.541 --> 18:41.125
Do you know what they did to him?

18:44.375 --> 18:45.291
No.

18:47.166 --> 18:48.416
Can you talk me through it?

18:49.458 --> 18:50.333
Hmm?

18:50.833 --> 18:51.916
Why?

18:54.625 --> 18:56.125
So you can help?

18:57.750 --> 19:00.000
Well, you already promised me that once.

19:01.500 --> 19:03.833
You looked me in the eye and promised me.

19:06.375 --> 19:08.916
But it seems you were busy
with more important things.

19:14.500 --> 19:17.250
I hope someone tells you
what they did to my son.

19:20.416 --> 19:21.916
I hope you never sleep again.

19:28.375 --> 19:32.500
Corinne. Corinne, wait.
Wait, wait. Corinne.

19:34.333 --> 19:35.500
Liar.

19:58.750 --> 20:00.625
Thank you so much for doing this.

20:01.541 --> 20:03.666
I never could have driven myself.

20:03.666 --> 20:06.083
Honestly, no worries. I...

20:07.083 --> 20:09.333
Anything that you need.

20:10.416 --> 20:11.708
Anything. You just...

20:11.708 --> 20:13.208
You just have to ask.

20:32.000 --> 20:34.958
<i>Police are yet to reveal
any official information,</i>

20:34.958 --> 20:38.291
<i>although we have been informed
that there are multiple fatalities,</i>

20:38.291 --> 20:41.416
<i>which occurred in a fire
shortly before midnight.</i>

20:41.416 --> 20:44.000
<i>We are awaiting further information
from the authorities</i>

20:44.000 --> 20:45.708
<i>surrounding the circumstances.</i>

20:45.708 --> 20:48.083
So, no neighbors.
Plenty of space...

20:48.083 --> 20:50.458
Excuse me, ma'am. There's a call for you.

20:50.458 --> 20:51.833
He says it's urgent.

20:51.833 --> 20:52.791
Thank you.

20:54.333 --> 20:55.166
DCI Raine.

20:55.166 --> 20:59.041
DCI Raine, it's, uh, DCI John Luther...

20:59.041 --> 21:01.125
<i>Well, I mean</i>, <i>it's not...</i>

21:01.125 --> 21:03.250
I, um, was a DCI in your department.

21:05.000 --> 21:07.375
Of course. I've heard of you.

21:08.208 --> 21:10.875
-<i>How did you get this call out to me?</i>
- Callum Aldrich.

21:11.583 --> 21:12.833
That was my case.

21:12.833 --> 21:14.625
I'm aware of that. Yes.

21:14.625 --> 21:17.541
<i>The killer contacted me and sent me</i>

21:17.541 --> 21:19.416
<i>a recording of Callum's death.</i>

21:19.416 --> 21:22.416
Now, he also sent me a personal message.

21:22.416 --> 21:24.041
Okay, I'm... I'm sorry.

21:24.041 --> 21:26.250
I can't imagine how that must feel,
but truthfully,

21:26.250 --> 21:28.541
<i>he has contacted everyone.</i>

21:29.041 --> 21:29.875
He did what?

21:29.875 --> 21:32.375
He sent recordings of the murders

21:32.375 --> 21:34.416
<i>to all eight families.</i>

21:34.416 --> 21:36.750
So why... why does he make an announcement?

21:37.250 --> 21:39.583
Why does he make
an announcement right now?

21:41.333 --> 21:43.500
I'll tell you why.
Because something's coming.

21:44.250 --> 21:46.833
<i>And whatever it is,
he needs... he needs an audience.</i>

21:46.833 --> 21:49.375
<i>That's the kind of personality he is.
He needs an audience.</i>

21:49.375 --> 21:51.791
- Read the room, John. Stop.
<i>- He wants us to see it.</i>

21:51.791 --> 21:53.291
Get ahead of him, get ahead of him

21:53.291 --> 21:55.500
and stop worrying about
where he's come from,

21:55.500 --> 21:56.875
<i>but where he's about to go next.</i>

21:56.875 --> 21:59.125
- I said enough! Enough.
-  Jesus.

21:59.125 --> 22:00.166
<i>Do you think I give a shit</i>

22:00.166 --> 22:02.500
about a dirty copper's
unfinished business?

22:04.416 --> 22:06.125
<i>Do you think I need advice from you?</i>

22:07.250 --> 22:09.250
You can't help me, John,

22:09.250 --> 22:11.291
<i>and God knows
you can't help Callum Aldrich.</i>

22:11.291 --> 22:13.250
It is still my case.

22:13.250 --> 22:15.083
No, it's not. It's mine.

22:15.083 --> 22:17.791
You abdicated yourself of that privilege
when you did what you did.

22:17.791 --> 22:20.000
<i>And... and you know, honestly, I'm glad.</i>

22:20.000 --> 22:22.083
<i>I am glad that you're ashamed.</i>

22:22.958 --> 22:25.375
<i>I'm glad that it hurts
to be where you are because...</i>

22:25.375 --> 22:27.083
<i>because it should.</i>

22:27.666 --> 22:29.875
Now, do not call this office again.

22:29.875 --> 22:32.791
If you do one call and
I will have you slammed up in solitary

22:32.791 --> 22:34.333
for the duration. Clear?

22:38.291 --> 22:41.458
Well done, Raine. I'm still a copper.

22:41.458 --> 22:44.208
<i>Ah no. No, you're not.</i>

22:45.791 --> 22:46.833
Not anymore.

22:53.291 --> 22:56.541
Put a call in to the prison governor.
Get that phone taken off him. Thank you.

23:02.625 --> 23:05.333
To be honest,
I don't know why you bothered calling.

23:06.125 --> 23:08.250
It's not even my area of expertise.

23:08.250 --> 23:09.666
<i>I'm basically a thief.</i>

23:09.666 --> 23:11.625
I'm not asking you to fucking marry me.

23:12.208 --> 23:13.625
<i>I'm asking you to do me a job.</i>

23:13.625 --> 23:16.416
It's not the job I've a problem with.
It's who I'd be doing it for.

23:16.416 --> 23:17.875
Oh, for fuck's sake.

23:20.875 --> 23:24.500
Look, I didn't trust you
when you were the right side of the law.

23:24.500 --> 23:25.583
Why would I now?

23:27.166 --> 23:28.750
Dennis, you been watching the news?

23:28.750 --> 23:30.875
<i>The Bishops Avenue thing.
Have you seen that?</i>

23:30.875 --> 23:32.750
<i>Have you seen what that prick has done?</i>

23:33.750 --> 23:34.750
Yeah, yeah, I saw that.

23:34.750 --> 23:38.625
So, you can... you can see
why I've got to get the fuck out of here.

23:39.916 --> 23:40.916
You're having a laugh.

23:46.875 --> 23:49.250
I know what happened to you
and to your mum.

23:49.250 --> 23:52.958
And I know that you were eight years old.

23:52.958 --> 23:55.458
That's why I'm calling you,
you of all people,

23:55.458 --> 23:57.333
because you hate pricks like this.

23:58.041 --> 23:59.000
And so do I.

24:01.083 --> 24:02.583
Yeah!

24:06.875 --> 24:08.416
So what are you asking?

24:17.041 --> 24:18.041
Stand still!

24:30.875 --> 24:32.583
Me being in here...

24:33.083 --> 24:36.333
I know it makes your life very difficult.

24:37.250 --> 24:39.083
Make me someone else's problem.

24:40.833 --> 24:43.125
Get me transferred out tonight.

24:43.125 --> 24:46.125
We can't make that happen by magic.
There are systems in place.

24:46.125 --> 24:47.541
I know what systems are in place,

24:47.541 --> 24:49.666
which is why you've gotta
let 'em have what they want.

24:49.666 --> 24:51.125
Let them come at me,

24:51.125 --> 24:54.625
so big, so loud<i>,</i>
that the system has to kick in,

24:55.416 --> 24:56.958
has to transfer me.

24:56.958 --> 24:58.500
- Let them at you?
- Yeah.

24:59.000 --> 25:00.583
How does that make sense?

25:00.583 --> 25:01.875
Because I'm ready.

25:03.166 --> 25:04.250
Can you do it or not?

25:07.291 --> 25:10.000
I mean, in theory, yeah, but...

25:11.000 --> 25:15.458
If it goes wrong, spins out of control,
you're a dead man. They'll kill you, John.

25:15.458 --> 25:18.208
All right, yeah. I... I can live with that.

25:20.625 --> 25:21.750
So let 'em come.

25:24.708 --> 25:26.500
Let them come.

25:28.416 --> 25:30.000
Get off! Get on the ground!

25:50.458 --> 25:51.541
Shit.

25:52.416 --> 25:53.708
Look. Shit.

26:09.916 --> 26:11.541
Now! All available staff!

26:19.750 --> 26:21.166
Ah!

26:42.875 --> 26:44.291
Get down!

26:50.583 --> 26:52.125
Grab that for him!

27:51.291 --> 27:52.208
Ah!

28:29.416 --> 28:30.375
Gah!

28:32.625 --> 28:33.541
Off!

29:04.166 --> 29:05.666
Stop! Stop! Stop!

30:22.125 --> 30:25.208
Don't fucking move!
Don't fucking move!

30:25.208 --> 30:26.666
Get on the fucking ground.

30:40.083 --> 30:41.916
-  Open the fucking door!

30:41.916 --> 30:44.708
- Come here! Move it! Open the door now!

30:45.208 --> 30:46.708
- There!

30:48.333 --> 30:49.708
Keep your hands still!

30:50.333 --> 30:52.375
Come on! On your feet! Move it!

30:52.375 --> 30:54.791
Move it! Move it!

30:55.541 --> 30:56.458
Move!

31:12.666 --> 31:14.041
- Boo.

32:10.250 --> 32:11.833
Mmm...

32:14.708 --> 32:15.791
I can't stay long.

32:18.958 --> 32:21.500
I just wanted to pop by

32:23.166 --> 32:24.750
and show you something.

32:35.125 --> 32:37.208
<i>Something was troubling her.</i>

32:37.208 --> 32:38.500
<i>She wouldn't tell us what.</i>

32:40.333 --> 32:41.791
<i>But she was scared of someone.</i>

32:43.875 --> 32:47.000
Who is she afraid of, do you think?

32:47.625 --> 32:49.458
Poor little Brigida.

32:49.458 --> 32:52.000
<i>...the worrying spike
in unexplained disappearances</i>

32:52.000 --> 32:52.916
<i>of young adults...</i>

32:52.916 --> 32:55.416
Oh, darling, no. No. Please open...

32:55.416 --> 32:56.791
- Open your eyes.
- Mm.

32:56.791 --> 33:00.416
<i>...surrounding Brigida's
disappearance have similarities</i>

33:00.416 --> 33:03.666
<i>to those of missing French student
Camille Fontaine</i>

33:03.666 --> 33:05.750
<i>and Croatian teenager, Jacov...</i>

33:07.083 --> 33:09.125
<i>Portuguese police are unwilling to...</i>

33:09.750 --> 33:10.666
You know...

33:17.375 --> 33:18.916
You always said...

33:20.791 --> 33:22.833
that I should talk to somebody about this.

33:22.833 --> 33:23.791
Mmm...

33:24.958 --> 33:28.500
And so that's exactly what I'm doing...

33:31.958 --> 33:33.125
because...

33:36.666 --> 33:38.333
<i>♪ I'm coming out ♪</i>

33:39.166 --> 33:43.791
<i>♪ I want the world to know
Got to let it show ♪</i>

33:44.708 --> 33:46.333
<i>♪ I'm coming out ♪</i>

33:47.208 --> 33:51.583
<i>♪ I want the world to know
Got to let it show ♪</i>

33:51.583 --> 33:52.541
<i>♪ I'm... ♪</i>

34:30.291 --> 34:31.916
Christ on a scooter.

34:34.625 --> 34:37.458
These the wheels you bought
from Fat Thommo Chitwood that time?

34:37.458 --> 34:40.541
Yeah. Five hundred quid
and a bootleg David Bowie album.

34:41.291 --> 34:42.250
Blue vinyl.

34:42.875 --> 34:44.166
Never let me down though.

34:44.916 --> 34:46.166
Never will.

34:46.166 --> 34:47.916
If you look after it,

34:49.041 --> 34:50.375
which you haven't.

34:50.875 --> 34:52.125
Yeah, well.

34:54.958 --> 34:55.958
Cheers, Den.

34:59.291 --> 35:01.166
I got you that thing you asked for.

35:06.125 --> 35:07.000
Perfect.

35:08.125 --> 35:09.166
Listen, Luther.

35:11.291 --> 35:13.791
When you take this prick to the ground,

35:15.333 --> 35:18.291
you do him grievous on my behalf, yeah?

35:19.416 --> 35:20.416
You do him damage.

35:28.666 --> 35:30.000
You take care, John.

35:32.125 --> 35:32.958
Yeah.

35:52.166 --> 35:53.291
DCI Raine.

35:58.458 --> 35:59.500
When?

36:02.416 --> 36:03.333
Okay.

36:10.916 --> 36:12.083
Okay, thank you.

36:13.208 --> 36:14.416
Boss? What's up?

36:14.416 --> 36:15.375
Luther's out.

36:15.375 --> 36:16.541
Luther's what?

36:16.541 --> 36:17.583
Out.

37:17.166 --> 37:18.625
Detective Superintendent Schenk.

37:19.791 --> 37:22.875
Just Martin. I'm retired.

37:22.875 --> 37:24.750
Well, they retired me.

37:25.708 --> 37:26.916
DCI Raine.

37:26.916 --> 37:27.958
Ah.

37:28.750 --> 37:30.041
My replacement.

37:30.916 --> 37:32.708
So how are things at the shop?

37:33.416 --> 37:35.375
Busy. Do you mind if I sit?

37:37.000 --> 37:40.000
I presume you've come for background
in the Aldrich case.

37:40.500 --> 37:41.500
But for that you're...

37:41.500 --> 37:45.125
I know who I have to go to,
which is basically my problem.

37:45.875 --> 37:49.500
Look, I know he's in prison,
but if all you need is background,

37:49.500 --> 37:51.208
I don't see an ethical conundrum.

37:51.208 --> 37:52.750
Except he's not in prison.

37:52.750 --> 37:54.583
But... Oh.

37:56.958 --> 37:58.458
Of course he's not.

37:58.458 --> 38:00.958
Listen. He's your friend?

38:00.958 --> 38:03.083
- He is.
- You know him better than anyone.

38:03.083 --> 38:04.625
You know how he thinks.

38:04.625 --> 38:07.208
If John really is your friend,
you'll find him,

38:07.208 --> 38:09.083
stop him nosing at my investigation.

38:09.083 --> 38:12.500
But if John Luther shows his face
and refuses an order to stand down,

38:12.500 --> 38:14.250
which we both know he will,

38:14.250 --> 38:16.250
Tactical Unit will shoot him dead.

38:17.750 --> 38:18.750
So...

38:19.875 --> 38:20.750
Martin...

38:22.083 --> 38:24.041
I'm not asking you to catch him for me.

38:24.541 --> 38:25.583
We can do that.

38:26.875 --> 38:28.708
I'm asking you to save his life.

39:51.000 --> 39:52.333
<i>Mum!</i>

39:54.291 --> 39:56.791
<i>Mum! Ah! Ah! Please stop!</i>

39:58.500 --> 40:02.125
<i>Hello again, John.</i>

40:04.166 --> 40:05.583
<i>Do you know who that was?</i>

40:05.583 --> 40:07.166
<i>Oh, I bet you do.</i>

40:07.166 --> 40:08.500
<i>Poor Callum.</i>

40:10.166 --> 40:16.958
The killer got to him
using an FM broadcast. 65.8 FM.

40:18.083 --> 40:22.083
Trace the frequency to source
and you'll find John.

40:22.083 --> 40:24.375
Out-fucking-standing. Thank you, Martin.

40:25.375 --> 40:26.541
Bring him in.

40:27.458 --> 40:29.250
Martin, what are you doing
the rest of the day?

40:58.208 --> 40:59.166
Morning.

40:59.791 --> 41:02.333
- I'm sorry. We're not open yet.
- I'm police.

41:05.875 --> 41:07.166
Can I see your badge?

41:10.250 --> 41:11.833
I forgot it in my other coat.

41:12.916 --> 41:14.083
Sorry about that.

41:15.291 --> 41:16.541
What's your name?

41:17.041 --> 41:18.000
Derek.

41:18.000 --> 41:20.750
Derek. Do you know who I am, Derek?

41:21.541 --> 41:22.833
I don't think so, no.

41:26.000 --> 41:28.291
You really don't know who I am, do you?

41:29.416 --> 41:30.541
I really don't, no.

41:33.250 --> 41:36.583
So how come you're broadcasting
the recording of a murder to me?

41:40.208 --> 41:41.500
Wait! No!

41:42.083 --> 41:43.000
Wait!

41:54.958 --> 41:57.250
-  You fucking...

41:59.750 --> 42:00.583
Sit down!

42:01.416 --> 42:03.083
And I want you to do me a favor.

42:03.083 --> 42:05.166
Sit there and do nothing silly.
Understand?

42:05.166 --> 42:06.125
Yes.

42:10.708 --> 42:13.000
<i>Archie,
we've tracked the signal.</i>

42:13.000 --> 42:14.583
<i>Sending the coordinates now.</i>

42:20.833 --> 42:22.291
- Where is it?
- In the cup...

42:22.291 --> 42:23.625
- Where is it?
- In the cupboard.

42:23.625 --> 42:25.791
In the cupboard. Idiots.

42:31.333 --> 42:33.041
- Have you listened to this?
-  No.

42:33.041 --> 42:34.375
- Have you? No?
- No!

42:34.375 --> 42:37.125
Good, because it's fucking horrible.
You know what it is?

42:37.125 --> 42:39.208
It's the dying breaths of a young man.

42:39.208 --> 42:42.291
A young man named Callum Aldrich,
and it's fucking horrible.

42:42.291 --> 42:45.166
And I want to find the prick
that made that recording.

42:45.166 --> 42:48.458
And you're gonna help me by telling me
how this transmitter got here.

42:48.458 --> 42:49.750
- I can't.
- No?

42:50.458 --> 42:53.916
Okay, right, well, this is the part
where I do something horrible to you

42:53.916 --> 42:57.208
like perhaps, I don't know,
tattoo your fucking eyeball.

42:57.208 --> 42:59.250
How do you turn it on? Turn it on! Go on.

42:59.250 --> 43:00.458
- There you go.

43:00.458 --> 43:02.541
- No, please...
- Don't move. Stop moving!

43:02.541 --> 43:04.625
Stop moving. Stop moving!

43:05.708 --> 43:06.625
It's all right...

43:15.875 --> 43:19.166
I'm not going to do that.
I'm not going to do that. Do you know why?

43:20.125 --> 43:23.208
I've got this thing,
and I've had it since I was a kid.

43:23.208 --> 43:25.666
It's kind of like a instinct thing,
you know,

43:25.666 --> 43:29.166
where you kind of look at someone,
and you read them.

43:29.666 --> 43:31.750
And you can tell
whether they're good or bad.

43:31.750 --> 43:35.458
I can tell, I can tell, Derek,
that you're decent.

43:35.458 --> 43:36.541
Yeah.

43:36.541 --> 43:39.708
So, I'm gonna ask you again.
How did that transmitter get here?

43:40.833 --> 43:42.041
It arrived by courier.

43:44.125 --> 43:46.458
- Is that a fucking joke?
- No, no, no!

43:47.166 --> 43:50.000
I was told to leave it running
for 24 hours and then ditch it.

43:50.000 --> 43:50.916
Go on.

43:51.416 --> 43:52.666
- That's it.
- What?

43:58.041 --> 43:59.958
Don't know if you've noticed,
but your game's up!

44:00.625 --> 44:02.333
The police are here! I'm here!

44:02.333 --> 44:03.458
Now, come on.

44:03.458 --> 44:06.416
-  I met a man online.
- Yeah. Mm-hmm.

44:07.541 --> 44:09.750
He was into extreme submission porn.

44:09.750 --> 44:12.208
We exchanged fantasies
for a long time, months.

44:12.708 --> 44:14.666
Decided to move things
into the real world.

44:15.666 --> 44:18.083
His needs were very specific.

44:19.250 --> 44:21.791
- He wanted to be taken by surprise.
- Right.

44:22.458 --> 44:25.375
He gave me his details. Name, address,

44:25.375 --> 44:27.416
time he got home from work,
the alarm code.

44:27.416 --> 44:29.041
Speed it up. Come on. Fuck's sake.

44:29.041 --> 44:32.500
One night,
I was waiting when he came home.

44:39.708 --> 44:42.583
There was a safe word,
but he didn't use it.

44:43.958 --> 44:45.541
So, I kept going.

44:47.875 --> 44:49.416
I just kept going.

44:51.916 --> 44:55.375
Because I hadn't really
been talking to him.

44:55.375 --> 44:56.916
I'd been catfished.

44:59.125 --> 45:03.666
Set up by somebody posing as
this poor man to assault him.

45:03.666 --> 45:06.083
He had no idea who I was
or why I was there.

45:07.666 --> 45:09.291
Armed police! Get back!

45:09.291 --> 45:10.416
And then what?

45:10.916 --> 45:12.083
-  Blackmail.
- Mm-hmm.

45:13.208 --> 45:15.666
The catfisher had it all on film.
All the things I did.

45:15.666 --> 45:16.750
Who was that?

45:16.750 --> 45:18.166
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

45:18.166 --> 45:21.250
No, I don't know! Just... Look... Just...

45:22.125 --> 45:25.416
I don't know him. I've never met him.
I just do what he tells me, okay?

45:29.708 --> 45:31.416
I've got to make this right.

45:33.083 --> 45:34.916
- I really do.
- Okay.

45:34.916 --> 45:37.291
- And it's going to be bad for you.
- I know.

45:37.291 --> 45:39.125
But it's not as bad as you think.

45:40.500 --> 45:42.291
Not if you help me catch this man.

45:42.291 --> 45:43.375
I can't.

45:43.375 --> 45:44.833
Oh, you can.

45:49.875 --> 45:51.583
For fuck's sake. What is it?

45:52.291 --> 45:53.625
- Hmm?
- He texts me.

45:56.333 --> 45:58.166
- Armed police! Armed police!
- Armed police!

45:58.166 --> 46:00.583
He never uses the same phone
for more than a day.

46:01.083 --> 46:02.833
You should have given me this earlier.

46:02.833 --> 46:03.833
I know.

46:05.791 --> 46:07.375
- Armed police!
- Armed police! Go!

46:08.500 --> 46:09.875
Armed police!

46:10.416 --> 46:11.666
All clear.

46:13.666 --> 46:14.583
Let's go!

46:15.875 --> 46:16.875
All clear!

46:31.208 --> 46:33.208
Have we got the place ready?

46:34.000 --> 46:35.125
It's ready!

46:37.666 --> 46:39.333
And the last of the livestock?

46:39.333 --> 46:40.916
En route and on schedule.

46:51.375 --> 46:53.500
So we're ready to go?

46:54.958 --> 46:56.166
We're ready.

46:56.958 --> 46:59.166
<i>Here's to the start of my new life.</i>

47:00.375 --> 47:04.791
I wish you could be with me
at the launch party.

47:37.208 --> 47:38.833
<i>Where do you wanna meet?</i>

47:50.958 --> 47:52.583
<i>Oh yes.</i>

47:52.583 --> 47:55.166
<i>Yes, yes, right there</i>.

48:14.458 --> 48:16.541
<i>- Oh my God! What are you doing?
- Oh crap.</i>

48:34.541 --> 48:35.375
Schenk.

48:35.958 --> 48:36.791
Wotcha.

48:37.375 --> 48:38.916
<i>I was wondering when you'd call.</i>

48:38.916 --> 48:41.833
<i>Yeah. I see
you're back in the shop then.</i>

48:43.125 --> 48:44.416
I'm consulting, yes.

48:45.000 --> 48:46.625
<i>Helping them to catch you.</i>

48:47.125 --> 48:48.083
Ah.

48:49.333 --> 48:51.250
Great work finding me.
How did you do that?

48:52.416 --> 48:54.375
Had a sniff around your cell.

48:54.375 --> 48:56.916
<i>Found the radio tuned to a dead station.</i>

48:57.708 --> 48:59.541
<i>I know you to be a Radio 4 man.</i>

48:59.541 --> 49:03.000
Yeah, well, that or the cricket.
That was very good work.

49:03.000 --> 49:05.750
Well, there's life in the old fucker yet.

49:05.750 --> 49:09.041
<i>Oh no, I never doubted it.
Are they listening in?</i>

49:09.666 --> 49:10.625
Not yet.

49:13.666 --> 49:14.583
I got him.

49:15.208 --> 49:17.041
What do you mean you've got him?

49:17.041 --> 49:19.041
Well, as good as. I got a number.

49:19.541 --> 49:21.291
<i>- How?</i>

49:21.291 --> 49:24.958
Doesn't matter how, but the number
won't be good to you lot. Not yet.

49:24.958 --> 49:26.458
They're not my lot.

49:27.416 --> 49:28.666
Yes, and given the fact

49:28.666 --> 49:31.375
<i>that it was obtained
by an escaped criminal,</i>

49:31.375 --> 49:35.500
I doubt there'll be much of an argument
for a warrant on the back of it.

49:35.500 --> 49:36.583
<i>Can you do me a favor?</i>

49:36.583 --> 49:37.958
Can you trace the number?

49:38.500 --> 49:40.208
<i>You know I'm not going to do that.</i>

49:40.208 --> 49:42.708
Come on, boss.
What are they going to do? Fire you?

49:43.208 --> 49:45.750
<i>One more time for auld lang syne,
and for what it's worth,</i>

49:45.750 --> 49:48.250
he uses burners.
The number won't be good tomorrow.

49:55.291 --> 49:57.250
<i>Call me back in 15 minutes.</i>

49:57.791 --> 49:59.250
Hey, do you want to put 20 on it?

49:59.750 --> 50:00.750
<i>On what?</i>

50:01.250 --> 50:02.333
Twenty that I get him

50:02.333 --> 50:03.791
<i>before you get me.</i>

50:06.375 --> 50:07.583
Make it 50.

50:10.541 --> 50:14.041
Well, he's got some onions on him,
I'll give him that.

50:14.041 --> 50:16.291
Look, I know how it feels.

50:16.291 --> 50:19.416
I've sat in the same chair,
expressed the same sentiments,

50:20.125 --> 50:21.875
but there's a double play here.

50:22.583 --> 50:27.083
Do as he asks.
Trace the phone. Give him a location.

50:28.166 --> 50:30.291
Luther's pulling us
away from the case.

50:30.291 --> 50:32.375
Look, the worst outcome is

50:32.375 --> 50:34.458
he's arrested and locked up by teatime.

50:34.458 --> 50:35.791
The best outcome?

50:35.791 --> 50:39.375
He's right
and leads you directly to your killer.

50:39.375 --> 50:43.041
Except if I were Luther, I'd assume
you and I were having this conversation.

50:43.041 --> 50:45.500
He knows. Of course he knows.
He just doesn't care.

50:45.500 --> 50:48.833
All he wants
is for this man to be caught and stopped.

50:50.583 --> 50:52.000
We'd have to go in heavy.

50:53.166 --> 50:55.416
The heavier the better, I should imagine.

50:56.000 --> 50:57.333
I thought he was your friend.

50:57.333 --> 51:00.833
He is. That doesn't mean
you should trust him though.

51:03.791 --> 51:05.791
All right, boss.
What's in the box?

51:05.791 --> 51:09.125
<i>- Deal or no deal?</i>
- The phone's at Piccadilly Circus.

51:10.125 --> 51:11.041
Nice one.

51:17.083 --> 51:19.958
<i>All units,
we're searching for an IC3 male</i>

51:19.958 --> 51:21.458
<i>in the Piccadilly Circus area.</i>

51:21.458 --> 51:23.541
<i>Do not approach the subject. Over.</i>

51:29.875 --> 51:31.666
Excuse me. Uh, excuse me.

51:31.666 --> 51:34.458
I'm running late to see my wife.
Mind if I make a quick call?

51:34.458 --> 51:36.750
I lost my cell phone. I'll be two minutes.

51:36.750 --> 51:41.166
Thank you. You are a lifesaver.
Thank you so much. Right, okay, thank you.

51:46.916 --> 51:48.291
So, where is he now?

51:48.291 --> 51:50.791
<i>Stationary
for the last 20 minutes.</i>

51:50.791 --> 51:52.541
Still Piccadilly Circus.

51:52.541 --> 51:54.208
<i>Something doesn't feel right.</i>

51:54.208 --> 51:55.666
What is he waiting for?

51:55.666 --> 51:59.208
<i>John, identify the target,
but do not engage.</i>

51:59.750 --> 52:00.958
I love you too.

52:02.000 --> 52:03.666
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

52:12.000 --> 52:14.291
All right, all right, Luther's on foot

52:14.291 --> 52:17.250
<i>in Soho en route to Piccadilly Circus.</i>

52:17.250 --> 52:18.166
Stay on him.

52:53.958 --> 52:55.416
Go.

53:32.166 --> 53:35.666
Okay, that's confirmed.
Luther's at Piccadilly Circus.

53:35.666 --> 53:36.750
<i>Do we take him?</i>

53:36.750 --> 53:38.583
Bravo unit. Ready to engage.

53:38.583 --> 53:40.625
Wait for Luther to ID a suspect,

53:40.625 --> 53:42.125
<i>then move in and take them both.</i>

53:42.125 --> 53:43.083
Received.

54:38.583 --> 54:39.708
Who is this?

54:40.208 --> 54:41.583
<i>You know who it is.</i>

54:43.333 --> 54:44.166
Move!

54:44.166 --> 54:45.250
Excuse me. Hey!

54:45.250 --> 54:46.541
Oh!

54:46.541 --> 54:48.250
- Stand back! Police!

54:48.250 --> 54:50.125
- Go, go, go, go!
- That's it. Let's go.

54:51.041 --> 54:52.833
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

54:52.833 --> 54:54.000
Stop! Stop!

54:55.625 --> 54:57.333
- Back.
- All right, just look at me.

54:57.333 --> 54:58.500
- Back! Back!
- Whoa.

54:59.166 --> 55:00.291
