Have we got a name?

1:19:08.541 --> 1:19:09.750
<i>Yeah, we got a name.</i>

1:19:11.250 --> 1:19:12.125
Okay. Who is he?

1:19:12.125 --> 1:19:13.875
I'm not going to tell you that, John.

1:19:13.875 --> 1:19:16.833
Can't have you pitching up at the arrest
turning everything into a circus.

1:19:16.833 --> 1:19:18.916
- I don't want that either.
<i>- Fine.</i>

1:19:18.916 --> 1:19:20.083
- I just...
<i>- I owe you.</i>

1:19:20.083 --> 1:19:22.458
<i>So you agree to meet me
at a place of my choosing.</i>

1:19:22.458 --> 1:19:25.916
<i>I want you cuffed in the back of my car.
No tricks. No games.</i>

1:19:26.625 --> 1:19:29.125
You can witness the arrest
before I hand you in.

1:19:29.625 --> 1:19:33.291
This is an offer, a one-time offer,
and it ends in five seconds.

1:19:36.666 --> 1:19:37.500
Can I trust you?

1:19:39.416 --> 1:19:40.875
Think we're past that now, aren't we?

1:19:44.041 --> 1:19:46.375
Right. Okay, yeah, fine.
But I choose the place.

1:20:22.166 --> 1:20:23.666
Evening, sir. What can I get you?

1:20:24.625 --> 1:20:26.375
Oh, I don't know. It's been a long day.

1:20:26.375 --> 1:20:28.583
What do you suggest?

1:20:29.083 --> 1:20:32.291
- I'd say a long day calls for a martini.
- No.

1:20:33.083 --> 1:20:37.541
Whiskey? We have an 18-year-old
Glenmorangie, uh, Tullamore Dew.

1:20:38.375 --> 1:20:39.791
I'll have a glass of water.

1:20:43.833 --> 1:20:47.750
If it makes you happy,
you can make it fizzy.

1:21:09.833 --> 1:21:10.958
DCI Raine.

1:21:13.958 --> 1:21:14.916
So who is he then?

1:21:14.916 --> 1:21:16.500
- I'll tell you in the car.
- Nah.

1:21:17.875 --> 1:21:19.041
Nah.

1:21:19.041 --> 1:21:20.000
Fine.

1:21:23.833 --> 1:21:26.416
Name's David Robey, city trader.

1:21:26.416 --> 1:21:29.125
Suspected aggravated sexual assault
six years ago.

1:21:29.125 --> 1:21:30.416
Never proven.

1:21:30.416 --> 1:21:32.625
A few months later,
his wife's planning to leave him

1:21:32.625 --> 1:21:34.625
until she's injured in a fire.

1:21:34.625 --> 1:21:37.083
Suspected arson. Never proven.

1:21:38.791 --> 1:21:40.166
Did the wife survive?

1:21:40.166 --> 1:21:41.875
If you want to call it that.

1:21:53.583 --> 1:21:54.500
Where's your car?

1:21:54.500 --> 1:21:56.208
Around the corner. Next right.

1:22:18.375 --> 1:22:19.208
Odette.

1:22:19.208 --> 1:22:20.666
Just walk to the car.

1:22:20.666 --> 1:22:22.083
What has he got on you?

1:22:23.875 --> 1:22:26.166
- What has he got on you?
- My daughter. So...

1:22:31.750 --> 1:22:32.666
- In.
-  Raine...

1:22:32.666 --> 1:22:33.583
In.

1:22:33.583 --> 1:22:35.958
If you do this for him,
you'll never get her back.

1:22:35.958 --> 1:22:38.625
- You must know that.
- I'll tell you what I know. I'll tell you.

1:22:38.625 --> 1:22:41.500
I know he never would have taken her
if you hadn't gotten involved.

1:22:41.500 --> 1:22:43.458
No. He'd done it anyway
as soon as you got close.

1:22:43.458 --> 1:22:45.791
He'd use her to control you,
which is what he's doing now.

1:22:45.791 --> 1:22:49.375
- Enough. Get in the fucking car.
- She's alive right now. Okay.

1:22:52.125 --> 1:22:54.875
He will kill her as soon as it suits him.

1:22:55.375 --> 1:22:57.458
- I said, "enough."
- And you'll be alive.

1:22:58.125 --> 1:23:00.083
- And he'll love that, so that you...
- Shut up.

1:23:00.083 --> 1:23:02.291
- Jesus Christ. Put that away.
- Shut up.

1:23:02.291 --> 1:23:04.041
- Get in the car. Get in.
- Put that down.

1:23:04.041 --> 1:23:07.166
He'll love it knowing
you could never admit what you've done.

1:23:07.166 --> 1:23:09.333
- The shame of it. Listen to me.
- Shut up. Shut up.

1:23:09.333 --> 1:23:12.375
He needs you right now,
and he needs your daughter.

1:23:12.375 --> 1:23:13.458
- Jesus!

1:23:13.458 --> 1:23:14.875
Get in the fucking car now!

1:23:14.875 --> 1:23:17.333
- Get in the car!
- I'm just saying we could use that.

1:23:17.333 --> 1:23:20.458
All right? To bring her home.
You and me, we could get her back.

1:23:20.458 --> 1:23:21.708
Odette!

1:23:22.666 --> 1:23:23.708
Ah!

1:23:36.500 --> 1:23:40.333
Okay, so if we do this, no one can know.

1:23:40.333 --> 1:23:41.916
Not, not Schenk, nobody,

1:23:41.916 --> 1:23:43.916
because he's got someone on the inside.

1:23:43.916 --> 1:23:45.333
- I know he does.
- How? How?

1:23:45.333 --> 1:23:47.500
I just know. I know him, okay?

1:23:48.000 --> 1:23:49.000
Get out.

1:24:01.291 --> 1:24:02.333
So what now?

1:24:05.125 --> 1:24:08.333
She's very weak.
It's very difficult for her to talk.

1:24:09.250 --> 1:24:10.291
Thank you.

1:24:13.958 --> 1:24:17.041
Georgette, I'm DCI Raine and this is...

1:24:17.041 --> 1:24:18.958
I'm DCI John Luther.

1:24:20.958 --> 1:24:22.833
I think you know what David's been doing.

1:24:22.833 --> 1:24:25.000
Please leave me alone, please.

1:24:26.833 --> 1:24:28.250
Afraid we can't do that.

1:24:30.458 --> 1:24:32.291
Archie, where's the boss?

1:24:32.291 --> 1:24:33.541
I'm not sure. Why?

1:24:33.541 --> 1:24:36.750
Oh shit. Um, nobody can raise her.

1:24:37.916 --> 1:24:39.625
She's probably chasing a lead. Why?

1:24:39.625 --> 1:24:42.083
Because Luther was right.
Something's coming.

1:24:58.333 --> 1:25:00.541
Jesus holy fucking Christ.

1:25:01.125 --> 1:25:03.750
People on-screen
match people reported missing

1:25:03.750 --> 1:25:06.791
over the last five, six weeks
all over Europe.

1:25:06.791 --> 1:25:08.708
Where's the site hosted? Can we track it?

1:25:08.708 --> 1:25:09.875
No.

1:25:12.875 --> 1:25:13.916
So...

1:25:16.000 --> 1:25:17.333
What... what happens?

1:25:17.750 --> 1:25:19.291
Users get to watch

1:25:19.291 --> 1:25:22.750
and vote for how they want
the victims to be killed.

1:25:26.375 --> 1:25:29.250
Listen, give me a second.
Okay, one second. I'll be right back.

1:25:42.208 --> 1:25:43.375
He's a good man.

1:25:45.833 --> 1:25:48.000
No, he's not a good man.

1:25:54.916 --> 1:25:57.541
I know you think
he sent us here to test you.

1:25:57.541 --> 1:25:58.916
But he didn't.

1:26:04.625 --> 1:26:05.666
Look at me.

1:26:09.333 --> 1:26:12.125
Here. Look at me, please.

1:26:18.125 --> 1:26:21.083
There's no reason on this earth
that you should be afraid.

1:26:23.416 --> 1:26:24.458
Not anymore.

1:26:30.083 --> 1:26:31.958
I know you tried to stop him.

1:26:33.708 --> 1:26:35.250
That's why he did this to you.

1:26:41.500 --> 1:26:43.125
We need to know where he is.

1:26:43.875 --> 1:26:48.500
And I know you can tell me that
because I know he enjoys telling you.

1:26:51.625 --> 1:26:53.958
Georgette, he's got my daughter.

1:27:22.833 --> 1:27:24.000
Boss.

1:27:24.625 --> 1:27:25.708
<i>John.</i>

1:27:26.833 --> 1:27:27.833
Where are you?

1:27:28.625 --> 1:27:29.875
In church.

1:27:29.875 --> 1:27:31.708
<i>They serve a nice pint there, do they?</i>

1:27:32.208 --> 1:27:33.166
They do.

1:27:34.166 --> 1:27:36.666
Listen, I'm calling to tell you
that I don't think we're looking

1:27:36.666 --> 1:27:37.958
for just one man.

1:27:37.958 --> 1:27:40.041
<i>I think we're looking for an operation.</i>

1:27:41.375 --> 1:27:42.375
What does that mean?

1:27:43.500 --> 1:27:45.000
They're running a red room.

1:27:45.500 --> 1:27:46.333
Red...

1:27:47.625 --> 1:27:49.791
Red rooms don't exist.

1:27:49.791 --> 1:27:51.833
<i>They're an urban legend.</i>

1:27:51.833 --> 1:27:53.291
Yeah, no, that's the point.

1:27:53.291 --> 1:27:57.250
I think he wants the world to think
he's a nightmare that's come true.

1:27:57.250 --> 1:27:59.583
That he's a bad dream,
and that he can touch

1:27:59.583 --> 1:28:01.500
<i>anyone he wants anywhere he likes.</i>

1:28:02.458 --> 1:28:04.791
Where is it? This red room?

1:28:06.208 --> 1:28:08.166
I... I cannot tell you that.

1:28:08.166 --> 1:28:09.541
I see.

1:28:11.041 --> 1:28:13.333
One last hurrah, is it?

1:28:14.208 --> 1:28:17.291
One last chance
to exercise that death wish

1:28:17.291 --> 1:28:19.708
you've been carrying around for how long?

1:28:20.458 --> 1:28:23.625
Boss, I'm sorry, okay?
I know that I've let you down...

1:28:25.708 --> 1:28:26.666
way too often.

1:28:26.666 --> 1:28:29.083
It wasn't me you let down.

1:28:29.750 --> 1:28:34.583
<i>The tragedy is that you are a better man
than you ever allowed yourself to be.</i>

1:28:50.625 --> 1:28:53.208
Well, look, I'm not going
to ask you to trust me, okay?

1:28:54.166 --> 1:28:56.625
<i>But I am going to ask you
for just one more favor.</i>

1:28:57.541 --> 1:28:58.583
Of course you are.

1:28:59.541 --> 1:29:00.375
<i>What?</i>

1:29:01.083 --> 1:29:02.375
Just check your texts.

1:29:08.291 --> 1:29:09.333
Can you do that?

1:29:11.500 --> 1:29:12.833
<i>How can I not?</i>

1:29:16.625 --> 1:29:17.541
Great.

1:29:57.291 --> 1:30:00.041
All I know is you
asked me to find her, and I found her.

1:30:00.041 --> 1:30:03.000
<i>I set up an alert on her passport,
and she used it.</i>

1:30:03.000 --> 1:30:04.083
<i>Hmm.</i>

1:30:04.583 --> 1:30:05.666
Used it where?

1:30:06.375 --> 1:30:07.416
<i>Passenger ferry</i>

1:30:07.416 --> 1:30:09.500
en route to Norway.

1:30:17.083 --> 1:30:19.375
And the investigation
knows nothing about this?

1:30:19.375 --> 1:30:22.291
<i>Well, that's... that's
a pretty time-limited situation.</i>

1:30:24.208 --> 1:30:25.875
Okay, good.

1:30:27.583 --> 1:30:29.166
Now, listen, Archie.

1:30:29.166 --> 1:30:30.916
No, no, you don't... You listen.

1:30:30.916 --> 1:30:32.291
Listen, listen, listen.

1:30:33.375 --> 1:30:37.000
There's only one person
that could have led DCI Raine to here.

1:30:38.166 --> 1:30:40.250
A woman, inevitably.

1:30:40.875 --> 1:30:44.708
<i>I need you to pay her a little visit.</i>

1:30:45.291 --> 1:30:47.375
<i>Make sure
she doesn't speak to anyone else.</i>

1:30:47.375 --> 1:30:48.666
Look. No. No.

1:30:48.666 --> 1:30:50.708
- Huh? Archie. Archie...
<i>- Please.</i>

1:30:50.708 --> 1:30:53.083
You can't just...
Can't you leave me alone now?

1:30:53.083 --> 1:30:57.208
<i>Listen, mate, you... you have come so far.</i>

1:30:57.208 --> 1:30:58.416
<i>There's no going back.</i>

1:30:58.416 --> 1:31:02.583
So I just want you to do
this one tiny weeny little thing for me.

1:31:03.125 --> 1:31:05.083
Yeah? And then that's it.

1:31:05.083 --> 1:31:07.208
That's it. That's... that's <i>your</i> way out.

1:31:09.583 --> 1:31:15.125
<i>Just think of it is as opening a door
to a future without me in it.</i>

1:31:21.166 --> 1:31:23.958
Odette, are you ready for this?

1:31:24.583 --> 1:31:25.750
I'm doing it. I'm here.

1:31:25.750 --> 1:31:28.083
Yeah? Whatever comes next?

1:31:29.958 --> 1:31:31.041
Do you have kids?

1:31:32.833 --> 1:31:33.666
Um, no.

1:31:33.666 --> 1:31:36.458
No, clearly not, otherwise
you wouldn't have asked the question.

1:31:37.125 --> 1:31:37.958
Ouch.

1:31:38.458 --> 1:31:39.416
Sorry.

1:31:40.708 --> 1:31:41.875
That was unkind.

1:31:46.166 --> 1:31:48.875
There was never enough time
for me and my wife.

1:31:52.750 --> 1:31:54.666
And then time just, um...

1:31:59.208 --> 1:32:00.250
ran out.

1:32:03.250 --> 1:32:04.583
I know you lost her.

1:32:06.166 --> 1:32:07.250
Mm-hmm.

1:32:14.083 --> 1:32:14.916
I don't get it.

1:32:17.083 --> 1:32:17.958
What?

1:32:18.750 --> 1:32:20.708
You seem like such a decent man.

1:32:20.708 --> 1:32:23.041
I don't understand
why you did the things you did.

1:32:24.416 --> 1:32:25.375
Well,

1:32:26.583 --> 1:32:28.125
I couldn't see any other way.

1:32:28.125 --> 1:32:29.083
To do what?

1:32:31.875 --> 1:32:33.166
What had to be done.

1:33:21.666 --> 1:33:22.958
I know. I'm so sorry.

1:33:30.541 --> 1:33:33.375
John told me someone would come for her.

1:33:35.583 --> 1:33:38.083
But he didn't know
who that someone might be.

1:33:40.916 --> 1:33:42.208
Oh, but I knew.

1:33:42.708 --> 1:33:46.875
So what does this man have on you, Archie?

1:33:47.458 --> 1:33:51.708
And how bad could it have been
for you to allow all this?

1:33:57.083 --> 1:33:58.666
You know, the funny thing is...

1:34:01.000 --> 1:34:02.541
it wasn't even that bad.

1:34:04.208 --> 1:34:05.333
Not really.

1:34:32.208 --> 1:34:34.416
According to Georgette,
we're three miles out.

1:35:19.208 --> 1:35:20.625
We're a mile and a half out.

1:36:36.708 --> 1:36:37.916
We can't stop.

1:37:03.041 --> 1:37:05.958
Mum. Mum!

1:37:07.166 --> 1:37:09.041
No, Mum!

1:37:09.041 --> 1:37:11.541
- Baby, no, no, no, no.
-  Odette. Wait. Wait.

1:37:11.541 --> 1:37:15.166
-  Help me!
- Oh my God. Oh my God.

1:37:15.166 --> 1:37:19.208
Mum!

1:37:20.458 --> 1:37:22.875
<i>Someone help me. Help!</i>

1:37:27.083 --> 1:37:29.208
Oh my God!

1:37:36.583 --> 1:37:38.000
Oh no!

1:37:47.291 --> 1:37:48.916
Okay... Hey.

1:37:50.583 --> 1:37:53.625
It should be you! It should be you!

1:37:53.625 --> 1:37:55.125
Oh my God!

1:37:56.375 --> 1:37:58.875
Get out. Get out.
Get out! Get out! Get out!

1:37:58.875 --> 1:38:01.916
Get out! Get out!

1:39:00.875 --> 1:39:02.541
It's not her. John.

1:39:03.791 --> 1:39:05.000
John.

1:40:19.750 --> 1:40:21.750
Hello, hello, hello, hello, hello.

1:40:23.750 --> 1:40:25.583
All right. All... all the cameras are on?

1:40:27.916 --> 1:40:29.416
Are we live streaming?

1:40:30.041 --> 1:40:31.041
No.

1:40:31.791 --> 1:40:33.416
Okay. All right. Let's go.

1:40:50.791 --> 1:40:52.791
<i>And three, two, one.</i>

1:40:54.375 --> 1:40:58.916
<i>Welcome to the Red Bunker.</i>

1:41:02.625 --> 1:41:05.000
All your votes are in and counted,

1:41:05.000 --> 1:41:09.708
and you're probably expecting us
to kick off proceedings with Brigida.

1:41:09.708 --> 1:41:10.625
Actually,

1:41:10.625 --> 1:41:13.833
<i>one of you asked if lovely Jacov</i>

1:41:13.833 --> 1:41:16.916
could skin her like a snake,

1:41:16.916 --> 1:41:19.791
which I... I have to say
really tickled my funny bone.

1:41:20.625 --> 1:41:26.666
But as it happens,
we have a surprise opening act for you

1:41:26.666 --> 1:41:32.208
as tonight's special guest is DCI...

1:41:32.208 --> 1:41:34.541
Well, no, actually he's not DCI anymore.

1:41:34.541 --> 1:41:36.916
John Luther.

1:41:38.291 --> 1:41:40.708
So, John.

1:41:42.125 --> 1:41:44.666
<i>I thought
I'd kick off by asking you as a...</i>

1:41:44.666 --> 1:41:47.416
Well, a bit of an expert
in these things, apparently.

1:41:48.541 --> 1:41:54.333
Do you think I can help being what I am?

1:41:55.541 --> 1:41:59.208
Do you think any of us can?

1:42:01.666 --> 1:42:05.250
Mate, I couldn't give a fucking monkey's.

1:42:19.666 --> 1:42:21.583
No, of course...
Of course you don't.

1:42:23.500 --> 1:42:27.041
Because you have got no idea

1:42:27.041 --> 1:42:29.916
what it's like to be born like us.

1:42:29.916 --> 1:42:30.916
Fuck.

1:42:31.875 --> 1:42:36.791
To live your entire life
not being able to express who you are

1:42:38.666 --> 1:42:43.333
for fear of people like you... policing us.

1:42:49.291 --> 1:42:52.041
But nobody needs
to be alone anymore now, do they?

1:42:52.041 --> 1:42:53.250
Hmm?

1:42:53.250 --> 1:42:55.000
Not even us,

1:42:55.000 --> 1:42:58.916
because we can create a place
where we can all come together

1:42:58.916 --> 1:43:00.750
to express ourselves.

1:43:00.750 --> 1:43:01.750
Ah!

1:43:04.416 --> 1:43:09.875
And to be safe.
To be safe from people like you.

1:43:31.541 --> 1:43:33.583
Mum! Mum!

1:43:34.541 --> 1:43:36.375
- Anya. Honey.
- No!

1:43:36.375 --> 1:43:38.833
- Oh my God. I'm so...
- Please!

1:43:38.833 --> 1:43:40.916
- No! Don't!
- No, no, no! Mum!

1:43:40.916 --> 1:43:42.041
- Please, no!
- Mum!

1:43:43.958 --> 1:43:45.666
You're a fucking piece of work.

1:43:47.541 --> 1:43:49.375
Leave her alone! Leave her!

1:43:49.375 --> 1:43:52.375
No. No, no, no...

1:43:52.375 --> 1:43:54.583
Stop it! Don't. Stop it!

1:43:54.583 --> 1:43:57.666
- Don't fucking touch her! Get it off her!

1:43:57.666 --> 1:43:59.083
Shush, shush.

1:43:59.083 --> 1:44:00.416
Listen.

1:44:00.416 --> 1:44:03.291
Listen. There is
a way out for her from this.

1:44:03.291 --> 1:44:06.000
Fuck you. Get off me. Stop it. Stop!

1:44:08.333 --> 1:44:10.250
Odette, do you actually want to stop this?

1:44:10.250 --> 1:44:13.583
Because you have the power to do that.

1:44:13.583 --> 1:44:16.500
Just say the magic word.

1:44:18.708 --> 1:44:19.541
Stop.

1:44:21.583 --> 1:44:22.416
Please.

1:44:27.791 --> 1:44:31.125
Now, I didn't expect
either of you two

1:44:31.125 --> 1:44:36.083
to pitch up this evening,
but since they have...

1:44:36.083 --> 1:44:37.708
Mum, get us out of here. Mum!

1:44:37.708 --> 1:44:40.583
What I would like to do is...

1:44:41.250 --> 1:44:42.125
Uh...

1:44:43.208 --> 1:44:45.791
Uh...

1:44:51.125 --> 1:44:52.666
I would like you...

1:44:55.166 --> 1:44:56.541
to stab him.

1:44:57.291 --> 1:44:59.791
Hmm. Would you
do that for me, Odette, please?

1:44:59.791 --> 1:45:02.708
Mum. Mum, don't do it. Mum. Mum!

1:45:02.708 --> 1:45:05.625
I... I can't do that. I can't do that.

1:45:05.625 --> 1:45:08.583
You can't? Okay, well,
